    feat(partition): run_random sequence-integrity control + confound HOLD
    
    Adversarial review of PREREG-A1 Phase-1 surfaced a confound: the non-IID
    partitions that lose to natural-by-BS (random_split, dirichlet, per_bs_dirichlet)
    are all ROW-level, so per-client build_run_sequences (partition-then-window,
    fl_v7) builds temporally-broken windows; natural-by-BS keeps runs intact. The
    +0.175 "advantage" may be sequence integrity, not BS-coherence. Centralized
    (BS-mixed, intact) 0.93 ~ natural-FL 0.916 >> random_split 0.74 supports this.
    
    Adds run_random partition mode (whole-(run_id,slice_id)-group random assignment:
    intact sequences, broken BS-coherence) as the decisive control, with 8 unit tests
    + V7Config "runrandom" naming + single-cell CLI choice. docs/SEQUENCE_INTEGRITY_
    CONFOUND.md records the evidence, the pre-registered decision rule, and a BLOCKING
    HOLD: do NOT submit JSAC / claim inverted heterogeneity is a RAN structural
    property until the 5-seed run_random gate (running on V100) resolves.

